subSubSection.paragraph:
Vitellarium posterior, central, compact, 26–35 × 17–26 (30 × 21, n = 14). Ovary antero-central, transversely elongate, bilobed, compact and becoming massive, dumbbell-shaped. Mehlis’ gland anterior to vitellarium. Vagina opens posterior to male pore, copulatory part 25–48 × 6–15 (36 × 12, n = 15), with strong walls, surrounded by a large but discrete muscular sphincter (
Fig. 25
). Proximal (conductive) part of vagina straight, thin, without cellular sleeve, with length similar to that of copulatory part; parallel to posterior wall of cirrus sac; connected with seminal receptacle in lateral field of proglottis. Seminal receptacle slightly convoluted, tubular, crossing poral osmoregulatory canal, poral to ovary.
